    "notes": "Principense (Lung'ie). Portuguese-based Gulf of Guinea creole; spoken on Prรญncipe island, Sรฃo Tomรฉ and Prรญncipe. Critically endangered: ~300โ500 speakers, mostly elderly. Part of the Gulf of Guinea creole cluster (with Saotomense/Forro and Angolar on Sรฃo Tomรฉ). KEY FEATURES: (1) LABIAL-VELAR STOPS: gb=[ษกอกb] and kp=[kอกp] โ direct retentions from Niger-Congo (Edoid/Yoruboid) substrate; highly distinctive. (2) PRENASALIZED STOPS: mb/nd/ng word-initial โ West African Bantu/Niger-Congo substrate. (3) NASAL VOWELS: nasality marked by following <n> (an/en/in/on/un). (4) SEVEN-VOWEL SYSTEM: a/e/ษ/i/o/ษ/u with both mid vowels phonemic. (5) AFFRICATES: tx=[tส], j=[dส], x=[ส]. (6) TONES: Principense has lexical tone (L vs H), though not conventionally marked in orthography. Language is the subject of active documentation efforts (SIL, SOAS).",
